    "en": {
      "title": "Sri Lanka warns about monkey measles",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Deputy Director General of Health Services Special Medical Specialist Hemantha Herath has said that Sri Lanka is also very cautious about monkey measles.",
        "He also mentioned that a proper program to protect the people of this country from disease has already been implemented.",
        "The World Health Organization has declared the outbreak of monkey measles a global health emergency.",
        "WHO Director-General Tedros Adhanom Ghebreyesus announced on Saturday (23) that the global outbreak of monkeypox represents a public health crisis that requires global attention.",
        "The World Health Organization considers monkey measles a significant threat to global health and has warned that it will escalate into an epidemic.",
        "More than 16 thousand people have been affected by monkey measles in 75 countries in the world and 5 people have died so far.",
        "According to data from the health establishment, the number of confirmed infections increased by 77% from late June to early July.",
        "Men who have sex with men are now reported to be at a higher risk of infection.",
        "Monkey measles, mostly reported from West and Central African countries, has also been reported in the United States, Australia, the United Arab Kingdom and European countries.",
        "Meanwhile, Indian media reported that the first case of monkey measles with no history of foreign travel has been reported in Delhi.",
        "While three people have already been identified in Kerala, the one identified in Delhi is a person with no foreign travel history, according to media reports."
      ],
